"title": "4642: fish",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4642",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A basic ingredient of diet in biblical times. Fishing was regarded as a trade rather than a recreation.</p>\n<h2>Fish as part of God's creation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:20-Gen1:22\">GEN 1:20–1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26\">GEN 1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:2\">GEN 9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:33\">1KI 4:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:8\">PSA 8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:39\">1CO 15:39</a></p>\n<h2>Fish as food</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:9-Matt7:10\">MAT 7:9–7:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:11\">LUK 11:11</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:17\">MAT 14:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:38\">MRK 6:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:16\">LUK 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:9\">JHN 6:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:5\">NUM 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:16\">NEH 13:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:34\">MAT 15:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:7\">MRK 8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:42\">LUK 24:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:13\">JHN 21:13</a></p>\n<h2>Rules about eating fish</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:9-Lev11:12\">LEV 11:9–11:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:9-Deut14:10\">DEU 14:9–14:10</a></p>\n<h2>Fish related to judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:18\">EXO 7:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:8\">ISA 19:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:29\">PSA 105:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:2\">ISA 50:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:3\">HOS 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:3\">ZEP 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Fish as the object of pagan worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:15-Deut4:18\">DEU 4:15–4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:23\">JDG 16:23</a> <em>Dagon was the fish god.</em></p>\n<h2>Fish involved in miracles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:17\">JON 1:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:4-Luke5:7\">LUK 5:4–5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:19-Matt14:21\">MAT 14:19–14:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:39-Mark6:44\">MRK 6:39–6:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:14-Luke9:17\">LUK 9:14–9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:10-John6:13\">JHN 6:10–6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:35-Matt15:38\">MAT 15:35–15:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:7-Mark8:9\">MRK 8:7–8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:24-Matt17:27\">MAT 17:24–17:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:5-John21:6\">JHN 21:5–21:6</a></p>\n<h2>Figurative uses of fish</h2>\n<h3>Fish as a symbol of entrapment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:12\">ECC 9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek29:4-Ezek29:5\">EZK 29:4–29:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:14-Hab1:17\">HAB 1:14–1:17</a></p>\n<h3>Fish as a symbol of the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:47-Matt13:48\">MAT 13:47–13:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:10\">EZK 47:10</a></p>\n<h3>Fish as a symbol of the resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:40\">MAT 12:40</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Fishermen as the first disciples</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:18\">MAT 4:18</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:16\">MRK 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>Figurative use of fishermen</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:16\">JER 16:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:19\">MAT 4:19</a></strong> <em>Describing the disciples' evangelistic role.</em></p>",
